-- Tax Reforms Attract Major Firms for U.K. Return, Telegraph Says
-- B y   S o f i a   H o r t a   e   C o s t a
-- 2012-07-22T09:49:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-22/tax-reforms-attract-major-firms-for-u-k-return-telegraph-says.html
As many as 15 major companies may
follow WPP Plc’s return to the U.K. after changes to rules on
taxing foreign profits, the Sunday Telegraph reported, citing
briefings by Commercial Secretary to the Treasury James Sassoon.  The firms, which weren’t identified, have appointed
accountant PricewaterhouseCoopers LLP to investigate the
transfer, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sofia Horta e Costa in London at 
 shortaecosta@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
